docs.lead_paragraph: Three new openers dominated the box office this weekend — each with its own robust audience. The animated "Lego Movie" spinoff "The Lego Batman Movie" topped the charts with $53 million, slightly less than the studio estimates from Sunday, while the "Fifty Shades of Grey" sequel "Fifty Shades Darker" opened in second with $46.6 million.

headline.main: Box Office Top 20: 'Lego Batman,' 'Fifty Shades' Open on Top
